news.title: Vasai-Virar civic body razes 41 illegal structures in Nalasopara
news.para: ​​There are 41 illegally constructed buildings and other structures in Nalasopara, and the court has ordered the authorities to pull them down.

news.title: Centre receives 28 proposals from 23 states to develop new cities: Housing ministry
news.para: In February 2021, the ministry announced that the central government would develop eight new cities to meet the demand for expansion of urban areas.

news.title: Primarc & RDB Group to buy business undertaking of DLF Techpark 1 for Rs 638 crore
news.para: JLL was the transaction advisor to both parties. Fox & Mandal were the legal advisors to RDB & Primarc. Shardul Amarchand Mangaldas & Co and PwC were the legal and financial advisors respectively to DLF.

news.title: Agra residents forced to vacate homes due to cracks caused by metro tunnelling
news.para: The damage, allegedly caused by ongoing metro rail tunnelling for an underground track, has raised safety concerns and sparked demands for urgent repairs.

news.title: ED attaches property worth Rs 1.5 crore of Tulsiani Constructions's director in PMLA case
news.para: The FIR alleged that the four flats booked by the aforementioned borrowers were mortgaged based on a tripartite agreement for a total loan amount of Rs. 4.63 crore, but the flats were not delivered to the buyers or the bank.

news.title: Macrotech Developers to acquire Janus Logistics and Industrial Parks for Rs 47.94 crore
news.para: "The acquisition is in pursuance of our planned strategy for calibrated growth in digital Infrastructure viz industrial and logistics," Macrotech Developers said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Road project connecting Dwarka to Delhi-Gurgaon expressway delayed due to encroachments
news.para: ​​The plan includes upgrading the stretch from IFFCO Chowk to Dwarka expressway via Sukhrali, Mahavir Chowk, Old Railway Road, and Basai Road.

news.title: REA Group alleges copyright infringement against rival Domain Holdings
news.para: REA said Domain had systematically sourced content from quite a number of realestate.com.au listings, which is owned by the firm controlled by media mogul Rupert Murdoch

news.title: Hong Kong's New World Development replaces CEO after two months
news.para: The sprawling business empire, run by Hong Kong's third-richest family, reported an annual loss of over US$2.5 billion in late September.

news.title: China's Evergrande liquidators file winding-up petition against Tianji Holding
news.para: "The Liquidators consider the winding-up petition against Tianji Holding to be in the interest of the creditors and other stakeholders of the Group," Evergrande said in a statement.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh government yet to provide land for Gaggal airport expansion
news.para: The airports at Shimla and Kullu and the heliports at Rampur and Mandi in Himachal Pradesh have already been operationalised under the UDAN scheme, informed the Union minister.

news.title: Goa: High court seeks replies on illegal hill cutting in Calapur
news.para: The Goa State Expert Appraisal Committee, in the minutes of its 172nd meeting on March 10, 2023, recorded that the deponent was illegally undertaking mining of a hill under the pretext of requiring the soil for making a service road in Survey No. 110/1 and 111/1 at Calapur village.

news.title: Patna metro rail to become operational from August 15 next year: Deputy CM, Bihar
news.para: In the build-up to the assembly elections due next year, the new metro rail would be a shot in the arm for CM Nitish Kumar development agenda.

news.title: Can't install CCTV cameras in house without resident's consent: Calcutta HC
news.para: Calcutta High Court ruled that installing CCTV cameras in a co-owned residential property without the resident's permission is a violation of privacy.

news.title: Nagpur property dealer arrested in Seoni for defrauding woman of Rs 42 lakh
news.para: According to the complaint filed by Gumgaonkar at Sakkardara police station, she had entered into an agreement with Paunikar for the purchase of a plot in Pimpaldhara, Hingna taluka.

news.title: Chennai civic body's commercial complexes remain vacant and struggle with low revenue
news.para: Despite being located in prime areas like T Nagar, Central, Anna Nagar, Ashok Nagar, and Alwarpet, these complexes struggle to attract customers, generating less than half of the ₹20 crore annual revenue target.

news.title: Bengaluru citizens form coalition to combat illegal construction
news.para: This initiative is in collaboration with several civil society organisations, including resident welfare associations, non-governmental organisations, Bangalore Apartments Federation (BAF), and active citizens.

news.title: Delhi LG approves reconstitution of construction workers welfare board
news.para: While giving his nod to its reconstitution, LG directed that immediate steps should be taken to implement Supreme Court directions to provide subsistence allowance to workers affected due to restrictions on construction activities because of high pollution levels in NCR states.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body halts construction of illegal apartment in Patia
news.para: According to sources, the real estate firm was allotted the land by the govt for industrial purposes, but instead, it started constructing a multi-storied residential apartment by illegally changing the type of plot to sthitiban.

news.title: Roorkee residents put ‘on sale’ notices on properties to protest waterlogging crisis
news.para: The road, which is around 60-foot-wide and connects around a dozen villages, has been plagued by waterlogging over a half-kilometre stretch for years due to the lack of a proper drainage system.
